						               													<description>Players divide into two teams, and take turns trying to come up with as many word association matches in a given category as possible, scoring points for correct matches.  The game ends when either team reaches a predetermined score, or when a predetermined time limit is reached.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are four categories:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Visual Imagery:  Try to come up with as many items as you can from the list on the card before your time runs out. (Example:  Things you see in a mall&amp;quot;)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Synonyms:  Try to come up with the indicated synonym for each entry in a list of words.  (Example: given the word &amp;quot;talk&amp;quot;, come up with the word &amp;quot;speak&amp;quot;; given the word &amp;quot;big&amp;quot;, come up with the word &amp;quot;large&amp;quot;)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Word Association:  Try to come up with as many associated words as you can from the list on the card before your time runs out. (Example:  Come up with words associated with the word &amp;quot;beach&amp;quot;)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sound/Letter Cueing:  Try to come up with the indicated item  from the list on the card, given the initial letter or sound of the word. (Example:  Things that are soft - starts with the letter &amp;quot;m&amp;quot; (marshmallows); starts with the &amp;quot;f&amp;quot; sound (fur))&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
